  50. ‌let check_consistency file_name unit crc =
  51.   begin try
  52.     let source = List.assoc unit.ui_name !implementations_defined in
  53.     raise (Error(Multiple_definition(unit.ui_name, file_name, source)))
  54.   with Not_found -> ()
  55.   end;
  56.   begin try
  57.     List.iter
  58.       (fun (name, crco) ->
  59.         interfaces := name :: !interfaces;
  60.         match crco with
  61.           None -> ()
  62.         | Some crc -> Cmi_consistbl.check crc_interfaces name crc file_name)
  63.       unit.ui_imports_cmi
  64.   with Cmi_consistbl.Inconsistency {
  65.       unit_name = name;
  66.       inconsistent_source = user;
  67.       original_source = auth;
  68.     } ->
  69.     raise(Error(Inconsistent_interface(name, user, auth)))
  70.   end;
  71.   begin try
  72.     List.iter
  73.       (fun (name, crco) ->
  74.         implementations := name :: !implementations;
  75.         match crco with
  76.             None ->
  77.               if List.mem name !cmx_required then
  78.                 raise(Error(Missing_cmx(file_name, name)))
  79.           | Some crc ->
  80.               Cmx_consistbl.check crc_implementations name crc file_name)
  81.       unit.ui_imports_cmx
  82.   with Cmx_consistbl.Inconsistency {
  83.       unit_name = name;
  84.       inconsistent_source = user;
  85.       original_source = auth;
  86.     } ->
  87.     raise(Error(Inconsistent_implementation(name, user, auth)))
  88.   end;
  89.   implementations := unit.ui_name :: !implementations;
  90.   Cmx_consistbl.check crc_implementations unit.ui_name crc file_name;
  91.   implementations_defined :=
  92.     (unit.ui_name, file_name) :: !implementations_defined;
  93.   if unit.ui_symbol <> unit.ui_name then
  94.     cmx_required := unit.ui_name :: !cmx_required

  151. let object_file_name_of_file = function
  152.   | Unit (fname, _, _) -> Some (Filename.chop_suffix fname ".cmx" ^ ext_obj)
  153.   | Library (fname, infos) ->
  154.       let obj_file = Filename.chop_suffix fname ".cmxa" ^ ext_lib in
  155.       (* MSVC doesn't support empty .lib files, and macOS struggles to make
  156.          them (#6550), so there shouldn't be one if the .cmxa contains no
  157.          units. The file_exists check is added to be ultra-defensive for the
  158.          case where a user has manually added things to the .a/.lib file *)
  159.       if infos.lib_units = [] && not (Sys.file_exists obj_file) then None else
  160.       Some obj_file

  162. ‌let read_file obj_name =
  163.   let file_name =
  164.     try
  165.       Load_path.find obj_name
  166.     with Not_found ->
  167.       raise(Error(File_not_found obj_name)) in
  168.   if Filename.check_suffix file_name ".cmx" then begin

  170.        Read the infos to see which modules it requires. *)
  171.     let (info, crc) = read_unit_info file_name in
  172.     Unit (file_name,info,crc)
  173.   end
  174.   else if Filename.check_suffix file_name ".cmxa" then begin
  175.     let infos =
  176.       try read_library_info file_name
  177.       with Compilenv.Error(Not_a_unit_info _) ->
  178.         raise(Error(Not_an_object_file file_name))
  179.     in

  184. ‌let scan_file file tolink = match file with
  185.   | Unit (file_name,info,crc) ->
  186.       (* This is a .cmx file. It must be linked in any case. *)
  187.       remove_required info.ui_name;

  205.            end else

  259. ‌let make_shared_startup_file ~ppf_dump units =
  260.   let compile_phrase p = Asmgen.compile_phrase ~ppf_dump p in
  261.   Location.input_name := "caml_startup";
  262.   Compilenv.reset "_shared_startup";
  263.   Emit.begin_assembly ();
  264.   List.iter compile_phrase
  265.     (Cmm_helpers.emit_preallocated_blocks [] (* add gc_roots (for dynlink) *)
  266.       (Cmm_helpers.generic_functions true (List.map fst units)));
  267.   compile_phrase (Cmm_helpers.plugin_header units);
  268.   compile_phrase
  269.     (Cmm_helpers.global_table
  270.        (List.map (fun (ui,_) -> ui.ui_symbol) units));
  271.   if !Clflags.output_complete_object then
  272.     force_linking_of_startup ~ppf_dump;
  273.   (* this is to force a reference to all units, otherwise the linker
  274.      might drop some of them (in case of libraries) *)
  275.   Emit.end_assembly ()

  310. ‌let call_linker file_list startup_file output_name =
  311.   let main_dll = !Clflags.output_c_object
  312.                  && Filename.check_suffix output_name Config.ext_dll
  313.   and main_obj_runtime = !Clflags.output_complete_object

  318.       files @ (List.rev !Clflags.ccobjs) @ runtime_lib (),
  319.       (if !Clflags.nopervasives || (main_obj_runtime && not main_dll)

  377. ‌let report_error ppf = function
  378.   | File_not_found name ->
  379.       fprintf ppf "Cannot find file %s" name
  380.   | Not_an_object_file name ->
  381.       fprintf ppf "The file %a is not a compilation unit description"
  382.         Location.print_filename name
  383.   | Missing_implementations l ->
  384.      let print_references ppf = function
  385.        | [] -> ()
  386.        | r1 :: rl ->
  387.            fprintf ppf "%s" r1;
  388.            List.iter (fun r -> fprintf ppf ",@ %s" r) rl in
  389.       let print_modules ppf =
  390.         List.iter
  391.          (fun (md, rq) ->
  392.             fprintf ppf "@ @[<hov 2>%s referenced from %a@]" md
  393.             print_references rq) in
  394.       fprintf ppf
  395.        "@[<v 2>No implementations provided for the following modules:%a@]"
  396.        print_modules l
  397.   | Inconsistent_interface(intf, file1, file2) ->
  398.       fprintf ppf
  399.        "@[<hov>Files %a@ and %a@ make inconsistent assumptions \
  400.               over interface %s@]"
  401.        Location.print_filename file1
  402.        Location.print_filename file2
  403.        intf
  404.   | Inconsistent_implementation(intf, file1, file2) ->
  405.       fprintf ppf
  406.        "@[<hov>Files %a@ and %a@ make inconsistent assumptions \
  407.               over implementation %s@]"
  408.        Location.print_filename file1
  409.        Location.print_filename file2
  410.        intf
  411.   | Assembler_error file ->
  412.       fprintf ppf "Error while assembling %a" Location.print_filename file
  413.   | Linking_error exitcode ->
  414.       fprintf ppf "Error during linking (exit code %d)" exitcode
  415.   | Multiple_definition(modname, file1, file2) ->
  416.       fprintf ppf
  417.         "@[<hov>Files %a@ and %a@ both define a module named %s@]"
  418.         Location.print_filename file1
  419.         Location.print_filename file2
  420.         modname
  421.   | Missing_cmx(filename, name) ->
  422.       fprintf ppf
  423.         "@[<hov>File %a@ was compiled without access@ \
  424.          to the .cmx file@ for module %s,@ \
  425.          which was produced by `ocamlopt -for-pack'.@ \
  426.          Please recompile %a@ with the correct `-I' option@ \
  427.          so that %s.cmx@ is found.@]"
  428.         Location.print_filename filename name
  429.         Location.print_filename  filename
  430.         name
